quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  53,1,"By the star when it goes down (or vanishes)."
  53,2,"Your companion (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) has neither gone astray nor has erred."
  53,3,"Nor does he speak of (his own) desire."
  53,4,"It is only a Revelation revealed."
  53,5,"He has been taught (this Qur’ân) by one mighty in power [Jibrîl (Gabriel)]"
  53,6,"One free from any defect in body and mind then he (Jibrîl - Gabriel in his real shape as created by Allah) rose and became stable."
  53,7,"While he [Jibrîl (Gabriel)] was in the highest part of the horizon, (Tafsir Ibn Kathir)"
  53,8,"Then he [Jibrîl (Gabriel)] approached and came closer,"
  53,9,"And was at a distance of two bows’ length or (even) nearer."
  53,10,"So (Allâh) revealed to His slave [Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم through Jibrîl (Gabriel) عليه السلام] whatever He revealed."